'''Ben Adams''' was a [[baseball]] player in the [[Negro Leagues]]. From 1953 to 1963,<ref>{{cite web|title=Ben Adams|url=http://www.nlbpa.com/the-athletes/adams-ben-2|website=Negro League Baseball Players Association|accessdate=29 July 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729231955/http://www.nlbpa.com/the-athletes/adams-ben-2|archivedate=29 July 2017}}</ref> he played for a number of teams, including the [[Kansas City Monarchs]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Powell | first=L. | title=Black Barons of Birmingham: The South's Greatest Negro League Team and Its Players | publisher=McFarland, Incorporated Publishers | year=2009 | isbn=978-0-7864-5480-8 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mfbaDBgpteAC&pg=PA57 | ref=harv | accessdate=2015-04-30}}</ref> and Fox Jeweler's City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nlbpa.com/news/november-18-2004|title=nlbpa.com - November 18, 2004|work=nlbpa.com|accessdate=30 April 2015}} Retrieved 30 April 2015.</ref>

Adams was from Norfolk, Virginia. He first played for the [[Indianapolis Clowns]] in 1953. He retired in 1969, ending his career with 11 years with the Monarchs.<ref name="bbkc">{{cite book|last1=Lester|first1=Larry|last2=Miller|first2=Sammy J.|title=Black Baseball in Kansas City|date=2000|publisher=Arcadia Publishing|isbn=9780738508429|page=85|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SYJeSYvOOdsC&pg=PA85&dq=%22Ben+Adams%22+baseball&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiIv76L0K_VAhWry4MKHT5SAl0Q6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=%22Ben%20Adams%22%20baseball&f=false|accessdate=29 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>

