{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Use British English|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox football biography |name = William Buchanan |fullname = William Duncan Buchanan<ref name="QPFC" /> |birth_date =27 July 1911 |birth_place = [[Balfron]], Scotland |death_date = |death_place = |position = [[Right half]] |years1 = 1935–1940 |clubs1 = [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]] |caps1 = 91 |goals1 = 4 | nationalyears1 =1936–1939 | nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national amateur football team|Scotland Amateurs]] | nationalcaps1 =5 | nationalgoals1 =0 }}
'''William Duncan Buchanan''' was a Scottish amateur [[Association football|football]] [[right half]] who made over 90 appearances in the [[Scottish Football League|Scottish League]] for [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]].<ref name="QPFC">{{cite web|url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/b/buchananwb.htm|title=QPFC.com – A Historical Queen's Park FC Website|last=|first=|date=|website=www.qpfc.com|publisher=|access-date=10 December 2016}}</ref> He represented Scotland at amateur level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scottish-football-historical-archive.co.uk/Forgotten%20Glories.pdf|title=FORGOTTEN GLORIES – British Amateur Internationals 1901–1974|last=|first=|date=|website=|page=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702210501/http://www.scottish-football-historical-archive.co.uk/Forgotten%20Glories.pdf|archive-date=2 July 2017|dead-url=yes|access-date=16 July 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
